-- Italy's bourse bans orders without price limit on Carige savings shares 
-- 
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 12:06PM EDT
-- None



MILAN, April 3 (Reuters) - Orders without a price limit on the saving shares of Italian bank Carige <CRGI.MI> will be banned on Friday, the Italian stock exchange said on Thursday.

Carige's saving shares <CRGIn.MI> closed 13.1 percent higher at 1.78 euros on Thursday.